WEBVTT

00:04.738 --> 00:05.873 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.906 --> 00:07.774 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.808 --> 00:14.314 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: The
Trump administration
takes on the government of
Syria, ordering

00:14.348 --> 00:18.352 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
airstrikes in retaliation for
chemical weapons
attacks.

00:18.385 --> 00:20.888 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We look at the decision and what
could come
next.

00:20.921 --> 00:22.856 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Then:

00:22.890 --> 00:27.594 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
We have made tremendous progress
in our relationship

00:27.628 --> 00:29.429 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with China.

00:29.463 --> 00:33.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President Trump
touts deepening
relations with China after his
first summit

00:33.567 --> 00:36.937 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with the leader of the world's
other economic
powerhouse.

00:36.970 --> 00:43.110 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: With Passover just around
the corner,
we join celebrated chef Joan
Nathan in her

00:43.143 --> 00:48.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
kitchen to talk about her new
cookbook exploring
Jewish food from around the
world.

00:48.315 --> 00:53.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOAN NATHAN, Chef: You can't mix
milk and
meat, you can't eat certain
shellfish, so

00:53.587 --> 00:57.190 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that what happens is, Jewish
people think
about their food a lot.

00:57.224 --> 00:59.226 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And it's Friday.

00:59.259 --> 01:03.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mark Shields and David Brooks
take on this
week's news, including what a
rule change

01:04.031 --> 01:08.969 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the Senate means for the
ability of the
two parties to work together.

01:09.002 --> 01:15.709 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All that and more on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:15.742 --> 01:18.478 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:18.512 --> 01:28.121 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The White House
says President
Trump has sent a strong signal
to the world

01:28.155 --> 01:31.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with last night's cruise missile
strike on
Syria.

01:31.124 --> 01:36.496 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The attack drew widespread
support today from
American allies, and
condemnation from the

01:36.530 --> 01:39.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Syrians and their allies.

01:39.666 --> 01:46.773 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A flash of light and the roar of
jet engines
lit up the predawn in the
eastern Mediterranean.

01:46.807 --> 01:54.114 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Two U.S. Navy destroyers fired
off 59 Tomahawk
cruise missiles.

01:54.147 --> 02:00.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Amateur video broadcast on
Syrian state TV
appeared to show the missiles
striking home,

02:00.621 --> 02:04.424 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the target, the Syrian
military's Shayrat
air base.

02:04.458 --> 02:09.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
U.S. officials say it was the
launching pad
for a chemical attack that
killed more than

02:09.296 --> 02:12.299 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
80 people in Idlib province.

02:12.332 --> 02:17.070 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Saleh Hawa, an opposition
activist in Idlib,
spoke to us via Skype.

02:17.104 --> 02:19.840 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SALEH HAWA, Syrian Opposition
Activist: There
is a kind of comfort among
people that, at

02:19.873 --> 02:21.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the end, after -- maybe after
seven years
of suffering and pain, at the
end, we have

02:21.541 --> 02:23.744 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
got a kind of ally.

02:23.777 --> 02:35.288 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have got a kind of protector,
you can say.

02:35.322 --> 02:40.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: News of the U.S.
missile strike
broke as President Trump was
meeting last

02:40.694 --> 02:43.930 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
night at his resort in Florida
with the president
of China.

02:43.964 --> 02:49.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
It is in this vital national
security interest

02:49.803 --> 02:57.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the United States to prevent
and deter
the spread and use of deadly
chemical weapons.

02:57.577 --> 03:03.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Both Russia and
Syria claim
rebel groups were responsible
for Tuesday's

03:03.116 --> 03:08.755 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
chemical attack, and the
Russians quickly
condemned the U.S. missile
strike.

03:08.789 --> 03:11.224 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov
spoke in Uzbekistan.

03:11.258 --> 03:14.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SERGEI LAVROV, Russian Foreign
Minister (through
translator): Of course this is
an act of aggression,

03:14.661 --> 03:17.030 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
committed on an absolutely
made-up pretext.

03:17.064 --> 03:21.034 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I hope these provocations will
not lead to
some kind of irreversible
consequences.

03:21.068 --> 03:26.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The Russian
Defense Ministry
announced that the U.S. attack
caused only

03:26.173 --> 03:32.245 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
minimal damage to the Syrian air
base, and
that most of the cruise missiles
fell short.

03:32.279 --> 03:38.718 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Indeed, opposition activists
reported seeing
Syrian jets take off from the
base today,

03:38.752 --> 03:40.754 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
heading for rebel-held areas.

03:40.787 --> 03:47.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But White House Press Secretary
Sean Spicer
said all 59 missiles hit their
targets, from

03:47.427 --> 03:49.963 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
fighter jets to radar sites.

03:49.996 --> 03:53.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meanwhile, Western allies backed
the U.S.
move.

03:53.200 --> 03:59.072 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In a statement, NATO
Secretary-General Jens
Stoltenberg said: "The Syrian
regime bears

03:59.106 --> 04:02.275 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the full responsibility for this
development."

04:02.309 --> 04:07.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
German Chancellor Angela Merkel
also defended
the U.S. action, but urged
caution.

04:07.814 --> 04:12.552 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANGELA MERKEL, German Chancellor
(through
translator): The attack of the
United States

04:12.586 --> 04:15.922 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is understandable, given the
dimension of
the war crimes.

04:15.956 --> 04:22.462 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At the same time, and I
underline, more and
more, it remains important and
right to focus

04:22.496 --> 04:25.165 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
all the attention on political
talks.

04:25.198 --> 04:30.904 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Turkey's
President Recep Tayyip
Erdogan said the missile strike
was fully

04:30.937 --> 04:33.940 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
warranted, but may not be
enough.

04:33.974 --> 04:38.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Syrian rebel groups also
called for even
stronger action against the
Assad regime.

04:38.445 --> 04:39.412 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Again, Saleh Hawa:

04:39.446 --> 04:41.348 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
SALEH HAWA: Right now, things
are different.

04:41.381 --> 04:47.020 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think, from now on, Russian
and Bashar al-Assad
and Iran and all those, you
know, naughty

04:47.053 --> 05:00.534 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
countries around the world will
understand
that, look, this is America.

05:00.567 --> 05:01.535 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
America today is different from
before.

05:01.568 --> 05:03.069 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
America is now ready to act.

05:03.103 --> 05:04.838 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The strike was in
stark contrast
to President Obama's policy.

05:04.871 --> 05:09.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He had warned of a red line
against the use
of chemical weapons, but backed
away from

05:09.876 --> 05:16.950 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
military action after a chemical
attack in
August 2013 killed more than
1,000 Syrians.

05:16.983 --> 05:24.357 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
During the campaign, Mr. Trump
also advocated
against military intervention in
Syria.

05:24.391 --> 05:31.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This week, he said the chemical
attack changed
his view of the Syrian war and
of Assad.

05:31.731 --> 05:37.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Trump had nothing to further
add today,
but at a U.N. Security Council
meeting, U.S.

05:38.004 --> 05:41.374 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ambassador Nikki Haley didn't
rule out further
action.

05:41.408 --> 05:44.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NIKKI HALEY, U.S. Ambassador to
the United
Nations: The United States took
a very measured

05:44.578 --> 05:46.613 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
step last night.

05:46.646 --> 05:51.484 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We are prepared to do more, but
we hope that
will not be necessary.

05:51.518 --> 05:57.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: On the diplomatic
front, the
issue is likely to top the
agenda, as Secretary

05:57.123 --> 06:01.795 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of State Rex Tillerson visits
Moscow next
Wednesday.

06:01.828 --> 06:06.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Congress, Democrats urged the
president
to seek congressional approval
for future

06:06.600 --> 06:09.636 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
moves, while Republicans
generally applauded
his action.

06:09.669 --> 06:11.504 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

06:11.538 --> 06:14.874 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN MCCAIN (R), Arizona: This
was a response
that was required in response to
the commission

06:14.908 --> 06:16.076 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of war crimes.

06:16.109 --> 06:19.379 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I want to emphasize, this is the
beginning,
not the end.

06:19.412 --> 06:21.715 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the signal that was sent
around the world
is very important.

06:21.748 --> 06:23.583 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

06:23.617 --> 06:28.688 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
EDWARD MARKEY (D),
Massachusetts: The president
has made a 180-degree pivot in
one week on

06:28.722 --> 06:33.393 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what the United States' role
should be in
Syria.

06:33.426 --> 06:38.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that, as a result,
the United
States Congress should be fully
involved.

06:38.298 --> 06:42.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We will get a
deeper assessment
of the U.S. strike, and its
implications,

06:42.802 --> 06:44.704 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
right after the news summary.

06:44.738 --> 06:48.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other news: The
long fight to
fill the vacancy on the U.S.
Supreme Court

06:48.942 --> 06:50.677 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
is over.

06:50.710 --> 06:54.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. Senate today confirmed
President
Trump's nominee, Neil Gorsuch,
by a vote of

06:54.881 --> 06:56.783 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
54-45.

06:56.816 --> 07:00.353 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He will fill the seat of the
late Justice
Antonin Scalia.

07:00.387 --> 07:02.322 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins has our report.

07:02.355 --> 07:07.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE PENCE, Vice President of
the United States:
The nomination of Neil M.
Gorsuch of Colorado

07:07.460 --> 07:14.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to be an associate justice of
the Supreme
Court of the United States is
confirmed.

07:14.134 --> 07:19.439 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The final vote
was almost
anticlimactic, after Republicans
triggering

07:19.472 --> 07:22.575 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the so-called nuclear option on
Thursday.

07:22.609 --> 07:28.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That change in Senate procedure
meant a simple
majority could break the
Democratic filibuster

07:28.148 --> 07:29.649 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
against Gorsuch.

07:29.683 --> 07:31.084 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Senate Majority Leader Mitch
McConnell:

07:31.117 --> 07:32.886 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

07:32.919 --> 07:33.720 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY), Majority
Leader: Of
course, I wish that important
aspects of this

07:33.753 --> 07:35.655 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
process had played out
differently.

07:35.689 --> 07:39.225 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
