moment, and
the question is, where will we
go from here?

08:09.589 --> 08:12.692 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Not all
Republicans were
celebrating the rule revision.

08:12.726 --> 08:13.693 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Arizona's John McCain:

08:13.727 --> 08:15.462 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

08:15.495 --> 08:21.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN MCCAIN: I am very concerned
about the
future, which will then, with
only 51-vote

08:21.301 --> 08:29.909 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
majority required, will lead to
polarization
of the nominees as far as their
philosophies

08:29.943 --> 08:31.811 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
are concerned.

08:31.845 --> 08:35.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But Minority
Leader Chuck
Schumer promised to protect the
60-vote threshold

08:35.482 --> 08:37.250 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for ending filibusters on
legislation.

08:37.283 --> 08:39.119 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

08:39.152 --> 08:41.121 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER (D-NY), Minority
Leader: I hope
the Republican leader and I can,
in the coming

08:41.154 --> 08:46.893 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
